item.title: Qld parliament withdraws media gag
item.description: The Queensland parliament has withdrawn a contentious bill that threatened to criminally punish journalists for reporting on corruption allegations surrounding politicians.

item.title: Qld records two new virus cases
item.description: Queensland has recorded two new cases of COVID-19 in the 24 hours to Friday morning.

item.title: New Victorian infections rise again
item.description: Victoria’s daily coronavirus infections have risen again with 372 new cases recorded overnight, taking the state’s total to more than 16,100.

item.title: NAB’s surprise profit result
item.description: National Australia Bank has posted a better than expected $1.5 billion net profit for the June quarter, despite ongoing financial pain from the COVID-19 pandemic on customers.

item.title: Seven straight days of rain for Melbourne
item.description: Melbourne looks set to be hit by at least seven straight days of rain as the weather gods give the lockdown city another reason to stay indoors.

item.title: NSW Premier’s major concern
item.description: NSW Premier Gladys Berejiklian says she is “worried” about the number of new coronavirus cases popping up where the source of transmission cannot be identified.

item.title: Jet skier found amid heavy fog
item.description: A jet skier missing for eight hours in Queensland’s Moreton Bay has been found, as Brisbane wakes to a heavy blanket of fog on the Friday public holiday.

item.title: Woolies’ new virus tactic
item.description: Woolworths will announce its first chief medical officer today in a bid to protect staff and customers from coronavirus - with his first task focused on the issue of masks.

item.title: Stolen car damages four at school pick-up
item.description: A man driving 100 kilometres an hour through a Brisbane school zone at pick-up time allegedly stole the vehicle before he crashed into three other cars.

item.title: Girls ‘assaulted’ at therapy
item.description: A former school counsellor has been charged, accused of physically assaulting two teenage students during therapy sessions at a high school in the state’s far south coast.
